commit.message:
Dropped upper version bounds of dependencies

It's to much work to maintain.

Fix build on GHC-7.2

This should fix #33.
Added Setup.hs so that cabal check will be happy on GHC <= 7.8.4

Fix build with ghc 7.8

Building with ghc-7.8 results in:

    Foreign: Can't be safely imported! The module itself isn't safe.

Keep `Safe` for ghc 7.10 and above but switch back to `Trustworthy` for
earlier versions. Tested with 7.8.4, 7.10.3 and 8.0.1

Closes: https://github.com/basvandijk/lifted-base/issues/31

h '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit.
lifted-base.cabal: Use https protocol instead of git
Make benchmarks compile with modern criterion

Fix GHC 7.10 warnings.

"Module Foo marked as Trustworthy but inferred as Safe."

Add a lower bound on monad-control for the test suite

This ensures the existence of the MonadBaseControl instance for ExceptT.
Unconditionally run ExceptT tests using transformers-compat
Support transformers-0.3 in the test suite

Work around use of ImpredicativeTypes

This fixes: https://ghc.haskell.org/trac/ghc/ticket/9569

Also bump version to: 0.2.3.1

Merge branch 'without-unicode-symbol-package' of git://github.com/minamiyama1994/lifted-base

Conflicts:
	Foreign/Marshal/Utils/Lifted.hs
	Setup.hs
